  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<img src=\"Art%20-%20Items/weapons/guns/rifle_square_roman-grigorev-021-dragonflame-rifle-2022-copy.webp\" /><p><strong>The Weapon</strong></p><p>This lever action precision-rifle is of unkown origins. Many modifications have been made to the mechanism and barrel, with most parts being replaced by a strange alloy (glaucite) that few outside of Numeria have ever seen.</p><p>The most recent modification to the weapon, is a gold-and-mithril-alloy wrapping in the shape of a dragon with its mouth as the barrel.</p><p><strong>Abilities</strong></p><p>With great focus the rifle can emit a cone of gold and orange fire, with potency relative to the will and power of its current wielder.</p><p><strong>Construction</strong></p><p>This weapon cannot be fitted with a bayonet, but its construction is so sturdy, magically reinforced, and imbued with unknown energy that it is nearly indestructable. As such, it can be used as a quarterstaff.</p><p><strong>Aura</strong></p><p>The weapon radiates good, and very potent magic. When fired, a muffled roar can be heard, and a wave of terror passes over the wielder. To fire this weapon requires a DC28 Will Save vs fear, or the wielder drops it immediately and is frightened for 1 round.</p><p><strong>Scope</strong></p><p>Using the scope requires concentration and a steady hand. It grants +2 to hit, but causes -2 to armor class for the round.</p><p><strong>Ammunition</strong></p><p>The weapon fires .308 cartridges and adds a touch of fire to every bullet it sends.</p><p><strong>Inscription</strong></p><p>Inscribed impossibly small etching on the black-steel barrel of this weapon reads:</p><p><em>Beloved Rovadra,</em></p><p><em>Immortal golden scales in flight,</em></p><p><em>Rolling golden curls by night.</em></p><p><em>She soared across the field of war,</em></p><p><em>And nightly came unto my door.</em></p><p><em>Felled at last by Tyrant's word,</em></p><p><em>Just one last time her love I heard.</em></p><p><em>She gave her soul unto my steel,</em></p><p><em>So her wrath our foes could feel.</em></p>",
      "instructions": "",
      "unidentified": ""
    },
